    "The CRF inquiries and image capture procedures were finely tuned to optimize acquiring essential, dependable data.",
    "For process consistency, common answers and options like \"None\" were included to preempt inadvertent errors and question skips.",
    "The questions were purposefully organized to mirror treatment steps, eliminating redundancy in clinician-patient interactions.",
    "In addition, because limited research has been done to evaluate the importance of different features in DFU healing phase classifications, we included most pertinent questions to extract as many key data elements as possible.",
    "As the DL-related research in DFU evolves, the CRF questions can be fine-tuned to be more specific."
